The paper deals with the problem of estimating the number of edges in an unknown graph using an independent set oracle. This problem is related to graph algorithms, computational complexity, information theory, and graph theory. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper involves graph theory and combinatorics, which suggest the categories cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as possible choices.
